SW Skills   
Strong software development skills are essential for making data scientists self reliant.
This module will teach you best practices for software development including:
use of design patterns, writing clean code, and updating/versioning/creating tests for a package.  

Learning Outcomes  
- using asserts to check conditions
- proper naming and coding conventions
- learn some essential design patterns (decorator, singleton, factory)
- create a virtual environment
- set up git repo to be installable
- install repo via pip
- create releases in github
- how to update a package
- how to create tests for the package
- how to tie package to CircleCI

